{How I help Muscular Distrophy}
My Mum and Dad have some friends who have a disease called Muscular Distrophy. They can't walk but have to sit in wheelchairs all the time.
We try to help people who have Muscular Distrophy by raising money. One way is by having sponsored events. My Dad had a{sponsored slim.}People gave him money for every pound in weight that he lost. I did a{sponsored {walk}with my friends.I raised more than Â£20 doing that. Another way we raise money is by having{car boot sales}on the pub car park. People put things they don't want, like toys, books, pots, into their car boots and then sell them.
